<h1>Conviction/Criminal History Information</h1>
<p><%= Customer.name_label %> will use the use the information on this form to conduct a criminal conviction background check. <strong>You are required to submit this form before working directly with a student under age 18.</strong> Please note that a conviction or criminal history does not necessarily disqualify you from participation in <%= Customer.name_label %>. All results are handled on a case-by-case basis.</p>

<%= semantic_form_for @mentor, :url => { :action => 'background_check_form' } do |f| %>

	<%= f.semantic_errors %>
    
	<%= f.inputs do %>
		<%= f.input :fullname, :label => "Name", :input_html => { :disabled => true } %>
		<%= f.input :aliases, :label => "Maiden Name/Aliases", :input_html => { :rows => 2 } %>
	<% end -%>
		
		<p><strong>1. Crimes Against Persons and Crimes Relating to Financial Exploitation:</strong></p>
		<p>Have you ever been convicted of any of the crimes listed below?</p>
	<%= f.inputs do %>
		<%= f.input :crimes_against_persons_or_financial, :label => "", :as => :radio %>
	<% end -%>
		<ul style="text-indent: 10em">
			<li>Arson (1st degree)</li>
			<li>Assault, Custodial</li>
			<li>Assault, Simple (or 4th Degree Assault) </li>
			<li>Assault (1st/2nd/3rd Degree)</li>
			<li>Assault of a Child (1st/2nd/3rd Degree) </li>
			<li>Burglary (1st Degree)</li>
			<li>Child Abandonment</li>
			<li>Child Abuse or Neglect (RCW 26.44.020) </li>
			<li>Child Buying or Selling</li>
			<li>Child Molestation (1st,2nd,3rd Degree) </li>
			<li>Communication with a Minor</li>
			<li>Criminal Abandonment</li>
			<li>Criminal Mistreatment (1st/2nd Degree)</li>
			<li>Custodial Interference (1st/2nd Degree) </li>
			<li>Extortion (1st/2nd/3rd* Degree) </li>
			<li>Forgery*</li>
			<li>Incest</li>
			<li>Indecent Exposure - Felony Indecent Liberties</li>
			<li>Kidnapping (1st/2nd Degree) </li>
			<li>Malicious Harassment </li>
			<li>Manslaughter (1st/2nd Degree) </li>
			<li>Murder, Aggravated</li>
			<li>Murder (1st/2nd Degree) </li>
			<li>Patronizing a Juvenile Prostitute </li>
			<li>Promoting Pornography</li>
			<li>Promoting Prostitution (1st Degree) </li>
			<li>Prostitution</li>
			<li>Robbery (1st/2nd Degree)</li>
			<li>Rape (1st/2nd/3rd Degree)</li>
			<li>Rape of a Child (1st/2nd/3rd Degree) </li>
			<li>Selling/Distributing Erotic Material to a Minor </li>
			<li>Sexual Exploitation of a Minor</li>
			<li>Sexual Misconduct with a Minor (1st/2nd Degree) </li>
			<li>Theft (1st/2nd/3rd* Degree)</li>
			<li>Unlawful Imprisonment</li>
			<li>Vehicular Homicide</li>
			<li>Violation of Child Abuse Restraining Order</li>
		</ul>
		
		<p><strong>2. Drug-Related Crimes</strong></p>
		<p>Have you ever been convicted of a crime related to the manufacture of, delivery of, or possession with intent to manufacture or deliver a controlled substance?</p>
		<%= f.inputs do %>
			<%= f.input :drug_related_crimes, :label => "", :as => :radio %>
		<% end -%>
		
		<p><strong>3. Related Proceedings</strong></p>
		<p>Have you ever been found in a dependency action, domestic relations proceeding, disciplinary board hearing, or protection proceeding to have: sexually assaulted or exploited, sexually or physically abused, a minor or developmentally disabled person OR to have financially exploited or abused a vulnerable adult?</p>
		<%= f.inputs do %>
			<%= f.input :related_proceedings_crimes, :label => "", :as => :radio %>
		<% end -%>
		
		<p><strong>4. Medicare&ndash;Medicaid/Healthcare-related Crimes.</strong></p>
		<p>Have you ever been convicted of any crime related to the delivery of service under Medicare/Medicaid or any state or federal healthcare program, or convicted of any crime connected with the delivery of a healthcare item or service? Have you ever been judged liable for civil monetary penalties for conduct related to the delivery of services, supplies or other participation in Medicare/Medicaid or any other state or federal healthcare program? Have you ever been excluded from providing services or supplies under Medicare, Medicaid or any other federal funded healthcare program?</p>
		<%= f.inputs do %>
			<%= f.input :medicare_healthcare_crimes, :label => "", :as => :radio %>
		<% end -%>
		
		<p>5. For all items checked in 1, 2, 3 and 4 above, specify the conviction or action date(s), sentence(s) or penalty(ies), imposed, prison release date(s) and current standing (e.g., parole, work release). For all items with an asterisk (*) above, provide a description of the victim including the victim's age.</p>
		<%= f.inputs do %>
			<%= f.input :victim_crimes_explanation, :label => "", :input_html => { :rows => 5 } %>
		<% end -%>
			
		<p><strong>6. General Conviction Information</strong></p>
		<p>Aside from those crimes listed above, within the past 10 years have you ever been convicted of or released from prison for any crimes, excluding parking tickets/traffic citations?</p>
		<%= f.inputs do %>
			<%= f.input :general_convictions, :label => "", :as => :radio %>
			<%= f.input :general_convictions_explanation, :label => "If Yes, indicate all conviction dates, prison release date(s) and the nature of the offense(s)", :input_html => { :rows => 3 } %>
		<% end -%>
			
		<p>I certify that the information contained in the above-stated information is true, correct, and complete to the best of my knowledge. I understand that consideration for participation in <%= Customer.name_label %> and the continuation of subsequent participation depend on true, accurate and complete representation of these facts as stated or implied in all application-related materials. I authorize <%= Customer.name_label %> to make inquiries regarding my education, work experience, references, unless otherwise stated, and criminal conviction history. I understand that participation may be conditioned on <%= Customer.name_label %>â€™s receipt of a satisfactory Criminal Conviction Report from the Washington State Patrol or other law-enforcement related agency.</p>

		<%= f.inputs do %>
			<%= f.input :background_check_authorized, :as => :boolean, :label => "I understand the statement above." %>
		<% end -%>
		
	<% f.actions do %>
		<%= f.submit %>
	<% end -%>
<% end -%>